article.headline: Chicago St 66, UMKC 65
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Tony Weeden scored 16 points as Chicago State beat Missouri-Kansas City 66-65 Saturday night. The Cougars (10-18, 8-6 Mid-Continent Conference) broke a 13-game losing streak against the Kangaroos (12-13, 7-7). Chicago State last won, 79-69, on Jan. 10, 1998. The Cougars had to hold on at the end. Royce Parran connected on four free throws in the last 26 seconds to give Chicago State a 66-63 lead. With just one-tenth of a second left, Brandon Lipsey was fouled on a 3-point shot. Lipsey made the first two free throws but missed the final one that would have forced overtime. Chicago State scored the first 12 points in the game. The first Kangaroo basket came on a rebound and follow shot by Carlton Aaron with 14:54 left in the first half. The Cougars led 34-27 at halftime. UMKC used a 14-0 run in the second half to take the lead. A 3-pointer from the baseline by Javon Clark gave the Kangaroos a 49-48 lead with 8:56 left. Chicago State's Rubeen Perry connected on a rebound basket at the 2:57 mark to tie the game at 59-59 and then hit two free throws to give the Cougars a 61-59 lead. Michael Watson led the Kangaroos with 17 points, Lipsey had 12 and Corey Starks added 10. Perry scored 14 points for the Cougars, Craig Franklin had 11 and Jeleel Akindele had 10. Mike English had career-high 14 rebounds for UMKC.
